2. the person playing canasta is somewhere to the left of the person playing whist##5
3. the person playing canasta is on the right of the person playing bridge##1
4. the person playing bridge is on the left or right of the person traveling to liverpool##3
5. the person traveling to new-york is on the left or right of the person playing bridge##3
6. the person playing backgammon is on the left or right of the person traveling to nizza##3
7. the person traveling to london is somewhere to the right of the person traveling to new-york##5
8. the person traveling to liverpool is not the person playing canasta##6

.:: Answer ::.
|            |   1   |     2      |       3       |      4       |
| Beverage   | liverpool  | nizza        | new-york      | london          |
| Job        | backgammon | bridge | canasta | whist |

